Package hw2

Class TimeClock

java.lang.Object
hw2.TimeClock
public class TimeClock
extends java.lang.Object
A TimeClock serves as a simple counter to simulate the passage of time. There is no actual connection to any real-world timer or clock. The passage of time is simulated by the method timePasses(). Time is assumed to be in minutes, represented as a single integer.
Author:
smkautz
